about.summary: Creates presentation-ready tables summarizing data sets, regression models, and more. The code to create the tables is concise and highly customizable. Data frames can be summarized with any function, e.g. mean(), median(), even user-written functions. Regression models are summarized and include the reference rows for categorical variables. Common regression models, such as logistic regression and Cox proportional hazards regression, are automatically identified and the tables are pre-filled with appropriate column headers.

name: r-gtsummary
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.6.0" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-gtsummary
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/gtsummary_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/gtsummary/gtsummary_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: dffd452c42f1b4b78a55af87bafab35d353f99a748ce84597516484dc2038753

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-broom >=0.7.11
    - r-broom.helpers >=1.6.0
    - r-cli >=3.1.1
    - r-dplyr >=1.0.7
    - r-forcats >=0.5.1
    - r-glue >=1.6.0
    - r-gt >=0.3.1
    - r-knitr >=1.37
    - r-lifecycle >=1.0.1
    - r-purrr >=0.3.4
    - r-rlang >=0.4.12
    - r-stringr >=1.4.0
    - r-tibble >=3.1.6
    - r-tidyr >=1.1.4
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-broom >=0.7.11
    - r-broom.helpers >=1.6.0
    - r-cli >=3.1.1
    - r-dplyr >=1.0.7
    - r-forcats >=0.5.1
    - r-glue >=1.6.0
    - r-gt >=0.3.1
    - r-knitr >=1.37
    - r-lifecycle >=1.0.1
    - r-purrr >=0.3.4
    - r-rlang >=0.4.12
    - r-stringr >=1.4.0
    - r-tibble >=3.1.6
    - r-tidyr >=1.1.4

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('gtsummary')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('gtsummary')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/ddsjoberg/gtsummary, http://www.danieldsjoberg.com/gtsummary/
  license: MIT
  summary: Creates presentation-ready tables summarizing data sets, regression models, and more. The code to create the tables is concise and highly customizable. Data frames can be summarized with any function, e.g. mean(), median(), even user-written functions. Regression models are summarized and include the reference
    rows for categorical variables. Common regression models, such as logistic regression and Cox proportional hazards regression, are automatically identified and the tables are pre-filled with appropriate column headers.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT

extra:
